{
  "uuid": "3be79346b22687c4d7ea7d3b5d4be1d0",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Manager",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>The HR Manager oversees and leads the <strong>entire HR function</strong> of the security company, ensuring <strong>full regulatory compliance, manpower stability, and effective workforce management</strong>.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead and manage full spectrum HR operations for the security company</p></li><li><p>Develop and implement HR policies, SOPs, and workforce strategies aligned with operational needs</p></li><li><p>Oversee recruitment, manpower planning, deployment readiness, and retention of security officers</p></li><li><p><strong>Ensure all office calls and HR-related communications are properly managed</strong>, escalated, and resolved</p></li><li><p>Advise management on HR risks, disciplinary actions, and employment matters</p></li></ul><p><strong>Security Industry & PRD Compliance Leadership:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure full compliance with <strong>PRD licensing and operational requirements</strong></p></li><li><p>Lead preparation for <strong>PRD inspections, audits, and regulatory reviews</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitor licensing, training compliance, and certification status of all security personnel</p></li><li><p>Act as main liaison with PRD, MOM, and other regulatory bodies</p></li><li><p>Oversee foreign worker matters including Work Permit compliance and audits</p></li></ul><p><strong>Payroll, Employee Relations & Governance:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee payroll accuracy, overtime controls, and compliance with employment terms</p></li><li><p>Handle employee relations issues, disciplinary cases, and dispute resolution</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper documentation and defensibility of HR decisions</p></li><li><p>Review and strengthen HR controls to minimise regulatory and operational risks</p></li></ul><p><strong>Leadership & Reporting:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage and guide HR/Admin staff</p></li><li><p>Provide regular HR and compliance reports to management</p></li><li><p>Drive continuous improvement of HR systems, processes, and compliance readiness</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements:</h3><ul><li><p>Degree in Human Resource Management, Business, or related discipline</p></li><li><p>Strong experience in <strong>security, facilities management, or manpower industries</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong working knowledge of <strong>PRD and MOM requirements</strong></p></li><li><p>Confident, firm, and able to handle high-risk HR and compliance matters</p></li></ul>",
